It created a buzz on social media  with some claiming that the forces of nature might have been violated.The remote village of Lusuati,in Igembe North- Meru county was reveling in mystery after a cow killed a lion in a rare act of bravery that saw the owner of the animal and other villagers scamper for safety. Several months later, our reporter Shukri Wachu visited the rare cow which has since been branded the ” lion slayer’  